1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","about 1120":"about 1120","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Goram","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably an altered form of English   Gorham  . It is found mainly in AL and LA."],"variants":[{"name":"Gorham","meanings":["English (Kent and Suffolk): habitational name from Gorham Wood in Bicknor (Kent), so named from Old English <i>gāra</i> ‘triangular piece of land’ + <i>hām</i> ‘homestead’.","English and Irish (of Norman origin): habitational name from Gorron, in Mayenne (France).","History: Born in England, John Gorham emigrated to MA and in 1643 married Desire Howland, daughter of John Howland, who came to North America on the <i>Mayflower</i>. His descendant Nathaniel (1738–96) was born in Charlestown, MA. He served as chairman of the Committee of the Whole House of Representatives in 1787, when it debated the American constitution."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":95,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":104,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"William de Goram was born about 1120, in England. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1120–":"umbes 1120–Surnud","1145–1204":"1145–1204","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1215":"1215","1204":"1204","1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","about 1120":"umbes 1120","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1120–":"noin 1120–Kuollut","1145–1204":"1145–1204","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1215":"1215","1204":"1204","1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","about 1120":"noin 1120","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1120–":"environ 1120–Décédé","1145–1204":"1145–1204","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1215":"1215","1204":"1204","1224":"1224","1145":"1145","1120":"1120","about 1120":"environ 1120","England":"Angleterre","lifeSum